Lach. places the mark of hiatus after 1012, giving a most involved explanation of the passage: his arrangement moreover is scarcely grammatical‚ as pateat is thus answered in the apodosis by imperfects and pluperfects. Indeed the lacuna does not appear to me so great as it did either to Madvig or Lach.: the poet has not only shewn already that the omne quod est, but also 988 (984)—1007, that the omne quod est spatium is infinite: he now, 1008 foll„ shews that matter is infinite. 1 formerly proposed roughly to supply what is wanting thus, Sed spatium supra docui sine fine patere.
